# Fix Verifier — plex state-dir ownership guard (fix.propose #2)
# task-1781916620-7cb8 debug:verify — 2026-07-15
# VERDICT: fix.verified

## What was under verification

The PRIOR verify round emitted fix.failed on ONE blocking defect: the regression
guard `test_runbook_has_no_uid_equals_gid_chown` could not detect the defect it
was written for. Its offender regex `chown\s+(?:-R\s+)?(\S+?):(\S+?)(?:\s|$)`
used `\S+?`, which cannot span the spaces inside `$((100000 + 999))` -> it
matched NEITHER the defect line NOR the fixed line -> no offender recorded ->
vacuous green. The runbook could silently revert to the bug-reproducing
instruction with CI green.

Bug Fixer #2 replaced the regex with a shell-token parser (_chown_spec /
_chown_halves): `$(( ))`/`$( )` opaque, split on the TOP-LEVEL colon, compare
normalised halves; PLUS an anti-vacuity assert (FAIL when parsed==[]).
Secondaries: (a) fail_msg `| int` coercion, (b) false single-offset-tile
invariant scoped to the uid map.

## [1] BASELINE — regression test on the restored tree

  .venv/bin/python scripts/test_plex_state_ownership_shape.py -> 7/7 exit 0
  "OK: no uid==gid chown remains in plex-claim.md (1 parsed)"

  `1 parsed` is COMPLETE coverage, not partial: plex-claim.md carries exactly one
  real chown command (:126); the other three `chown` hits (:130, :132, :147) are
  prose with no owner:group spec and are correctly ignored (spec parses, no
  top-level colon -> halves None). grep over docs/ finds no other chown COMMAND
  (usb-media-mounts.md:109 and das-zfs-migration.md:145 are prose), so scoping
  the guard to plex-claim.md leaves no gap.

