## RESIDUAL (non-blocking, recorded — NOT grounds for fix.failed)

The offender test compares the two halves TEXTUALLY. A collapse spelled with
textually-different-but-semantically-equal halves (e.g.
`$((100000 + plex_uid)):$((100000 + 999))` when plex_uid==999) would not be
flagged. This is contrived, it is strictly narrower than the defect actually
reported, and the anti-vacuity assert means the guard can never again go green
by parsing nothing — the failure mode that caused the prior fix.failed. Shape
guard, not a semantic evaluator. Noted for the record only.

## VERDICT

fix.verified — the blocking defect is fixed (Probe A + the 1/29 gate FAIL prove
the guard now sees the exact line it was blind to), both secondaries are fixed
and independently confirmed (Jinja2 render + live 110.conf), the live harness is
4/4 blocking, and the focused suite is GATE PASS 29/29 exit 0.
